## Context tree

Per-area conventions live in nested `AGENTS.md` nodes, each paired with a one-line `CLAUDE.md` (`@AGENTS.md`) so Claude Code's descendant walker finds them:

| Node | Covers |
|---|---|
| `docs/plans/AGENTS.md` | plan lifecycle + conventions |
| `plugins/{{ plugin_name }}/skills/AGENTS.md` | skill authoring rules |
| `scripts/AGENTS.md` | validators + CI |

The `context-tree` skill maintains these nodes; `scripts/tree/guard.mjs` enforces the pair convention.

## Codex plan agents

The plan contract has five exact owners: `plan-workspace` bootstraps, migrates, audits, or explicitly refreshes the workspace; public `plan-creator` drafts, self-reviews, and commits one previously nonexistent plan; public `plan-manager` owns every existing-plan operation—including guarded `publish <slug> as an issue` / `--issues` GitHub issue publication—review orchestration, prepared-request and candidate-commitment commits, terminal-family validation, receipt, and lifecycle write; internal `plan-reviewer` returns sealed-bundle evidence; and internal `plan-repairer` returns one exact accepted-blocker patch or `cannot_repair`. Only `.codex/agents/plan-manager.toml` and `.codex/agents/plan-reviewer.toml` exist as repo-local wrappers; the other three skills run without wrappers. For creation, manager proves the canonical path is missing and routes to creator, creator returns the closed `PlanCreatedV1` handoff, and main context may separately invoke manager review with lifecycle intent `none`. Current schema 6 commits and reads back the exact prepared request before controller construction, then commits and reads back each candidate's exact-600 dispatch commitment before spawn. Repair advancement atomically removes the round-one request/commitment before a separate round-two prepared-request commit. Only the current user authorizes abandonment; main-context manager alone may persist that exact-byte authorization or a source-plan-bound config abort. It validates reducer output with `validateReviewTerminalFamily({currentPlanBytes,parentPlanBytes})` before commit and again on the committed child plus its exact single parent. StateV2 embeds the exact active source state, and both terminal families are disjoint, receiptless, seriesless, nonretryable, and apply-ineligible. Current schema 6 uses one `gpt-5.6-sol`/high/Standard primary reviewer, with Claude Fable/high then Opus/xhigh as availability-only fallbacks. Main-context manager alone dispatches review, reconciles findings, writes persisted orchestration and receipts, applies lifecycle, and may call repairer once for the complete accepted independently reproduced blocking set. Reviewer remains evidence-only; repairer remains patch-only and neither can commit or abandon. Review has one full round plus at most one changed-input repair round; Session Relay is invalid evidence. Historical schemas 1–5 are validation-only and retain their exact persisted meanings.

Every prepared request and exact-600 dispatch commitment is written/read back
in a separate plan-only commit before launch. `buildReviewerArgv` is
derivation-only. `dispatchCommittedReviewer` is the sole consuming process
boundary: it reads exact current-HEAD, single-parent plan-only Git bytes,
matches expected request/commitment hashes and actual proposed
`orchestrator_tool/600` config/committed argv, then calls trusted
`controllerAdapter.dispatch` once with committed values. Invalid or substituted
paths call it zero times,
and no argv/commitment result is reusable launch authorization.

Each commitment hash-binds exact validated `prior_attempts`; candidate index
equals their length, index 0 uses `[]`, and later entries are ordered
availability-only evidence. The gate rederives argv with that array and requires
matching earlier-candidate commitments in parent Git history. Missing or
substituted prior evidence or a missing parent commitment calls the adapter zero
times.

Before commitment, manager verifies the sealed bundle path/digest and prepares
a safe schema-6 Codex workspace. Commitment deep-copies its record/hash; Claude
uses null. The gate independently rechecks bundle plus workspace root/path,
owner/mode, non-symlink, and sentinel, then rederives argv. Proposed config
comparison covers only candidate index, argv/hash, and timeout fields.

The gate also compares current worktree plan bytes byte-for-byte to
`git show <committedPlanCommit>:<planPath>` (or enforces equivalent path
cleanliness); uncommitted post-commit drift calls the adapter zero times.

Terminal reducer output is checked with
`validateReviewTerminalFamily({currentPlanBytes,parentPlanBytes})` before
commit and again from the committed child and exact single-parent plan blobs.
Administrative abandonment is source-plan/state-bound and persists canonical
base64 plus SHA-256 of the current user's exact UTF-8 authorization bytes.

Full project CI and acceptance evidence run once at the implementation boundary
and bind to the implementation tree plus `affected_paths`. Plan-only state,
request, commitment, and lifecycle commits may reuse green evidence only while
that tree and those paths are unchanged; machine-family validation and plan
read-back still run after every plan-only commit. Any implementation-tree or
affected-path change invalidates reuse and requires fresh full project CI and
acceptance evidence, while release-tag and final implementation CI remain authoritative.

The bound implementation identity is SHA-256 of compact JCS over sorted
`affected_paths` entries. Each entry binds the exact repo-relative path, Git
kind/mode, and blob SHA-256, or an explicit tombstone for absence. Exclude the
plan/orchestration path unless it is itself an affected implementation path.
Before reuse, recompute and require exact digest equality. A plan-only metadata
or orchestration commit preserves the digest; any affected-path byte, mode,
kind, or presence change invalidates it and requires fresh full project CI and
acceptance evidence. This contract does not change closed review-policy schemas.

Completion consumes and validates the bound green project-CI evidence when the
affected-path digest is unchanged. The disposable helper runs project CI only
when no eligible bound result exists or the digest changed; it must not rerun
merely because completion review began. Acceptance rows still run once as
required.

CI evidence reuse is the churn/performance fix; it never collapses authorization
commits. Active-state, prepared-request, and dispatch-commitment commits MUST
remain separate because each later artifact is derived only after committed
read-back of its predecessor. Combining them atomically is forbidden.

If an active plan changes the canonical review controller, manager, or reviewer
mechanism used for its own completion, same-checkout self-dispatch is forbidden.
Return `NeedsUserAction`; require an independent trusted released or pinned
bootstrap reviewer path, or a later fresh session. Never repair, reseal, or
replace orchestration in place to bypass this boundary. `stopped`, `stuck`, and
attempt-2 failure return `NeedsUserAction` without automatic reprepare or retry.

## Tool-agnostic rules

- Run `corepack enable && pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` once, then `node scripts/tree/guard.mjs` and `node scripts/skills/guard.mjs plugins/{{ plugin_name }}/skills` before commit
- Skill bodies stay ≤500 lines per agentskills.io spec (sweet spot 80–310)
- Manifest versions stay in lockstep across both `plugin.json`s and both marketplace catalogs
